Howard POTTER and The Powell Pressed Steel Company v. The MADISON WILLOW CRAFT COMPANY. No. 7506. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Nov. 11, 1936. Kwis, Hudson & Kent, of Qeveland, Ohio, for appellants. J. Harrow Leonard, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

' On motion of counsel for appellant, it is ordered that this case be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs to be assessed against the appellant.
